bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: This collection of little magazines was assembled over a period of several years. For purposes of this collection little magazines were defined as having primary emphasis on the arts; magazines with primary emphasis on politics---sexual, racial, economic, etc.--- were excluded from the collection. It will be found that a majority of these magazines are primarily or exclusively devoted to poetry. The collection is a sampling, both of little magazines as a group and of any specific magazines.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized alphabetically by title.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Collection consists of single issues, partial and complete runs of approximately 615 little magazines, published chiefly from 1965 to 1976. Primary emphasis is on the arts, with the majority devoted to poetry. Most of the periodicals are published in the United States; other countries represented are Mexico, Ecuador, Colombia, Argentina, Venezuela, South Africa, Kenya, Australia, India, Norway, Great Britain, France, Germany, and Canada. Arizona publications include Poet's Calliope; The Desert Rune; and Changes.
